 footballer)|Jim Craig]]\n* [[Paddy Crerand]]\n* [[Kenny Dalglish]] [[Member of the Most Excellent Order of the British Empire|MBE]]\n* [[Jimmy Delaney]]\n* [[Bobby Evans]]\n{{col-3}}\n* [[Tommy Gemmell]]\n* [[Mo Johnston]]\n* [[Jimmy Johnstone]]\n* [[Paul Lambert]]\n* [[Henrik Larsson]]\n* [[Bobby Lennox]]\n* [[Willie Maley]]\n* [[Danny McGrain]]\n* [[Jimmy McGrory]]\n{{col-3}}\n* [[Billy McNeill]]\n* [[Paul McStay]]\n* [[Bobby Murdoch]]\n* [[Charlie Nicholas]]\n* [[Ronnie Simpson]]\n* [[Jock Stein]] [[CBE]]\n* [[Gordon Strachan]]\n* [[John Thomson (footballer, born 1909)|John Thomson]]\n* [[Willie Wallace]]\n{{col-end}}\n\n===Scotland Roll of Honour===\nThe [[Scotland national football team roll of honour]] recognises players who have gained 50 or more international caps for Scotland. Inductees to have played for Celtic are:<ref name=SFARoll>{{cite web|url=http://www.scotlandfootballstats.co.uk/players/sfa-hall-of-fame |work=Scotland Football Stats |accessdate=27 February 2017|title=SFA Hall of Fame}}</ref>\n\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n* [[Roy Aitken]] (50)\n* [[Tom Boyd (Scottish footballer)|Tom Boyd]] (66)\n* [[Scott Brown (footballer, born June 1985)|Scott Brown]] (52)\n* [[Gary Caldwell]] (17)\n* [[John Collins (footballer born 1968)|John Collins]] (32)\n{{col-2}}\n* [[Kenny Dalglish]] [[Member of the Most Excellent Order of the British Empire|MBE]] (47)\n* [[Craig Gordon]] (14)\n* [[Danny McGrain]] [[Member of the Most Excellent Order of the British Empire|MBE]] (62)\n* [[Paul McStay]] (76)\n* [[Kenny Miller]] (7)\n{{col-end}}\n\nNumbers in brackets indicate the number of caps the above players won whilst at Celtic.<ref name = \"lh\">{{cite web |url=http://www.fitbastats.com/scotland/domestic_caps_per_player.php?club=42 |work=Fitbastats |title=Players Capped When Playing With Celtic |accessdate=19 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Scottish Sports Hall of Fame===\nIn the [[Scottish Sports Hall of Fame]], five Celtic players have been selected, they are:\n\n* [[Knight Bachelor|Sir]] [[Kenny Dalglish]] [[Member of the Most Excellent Order of the British Empire|MBE]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sshf.co.uk/inductees/a-f/kenny-dalglish-mbe/ |title=Kenny Dalglish, MBE |website=Scottish Sports Hall of Fame |year=2002 |accessdate=7 December 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151005143759/http://www.sshf.co.uk/inductees/a-f/kenny-dalglish-mbe/ |archive-date=5 October 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* [[Jimmy Johnstone]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sshf.co.uk/inductees/g-k/jimmy-johnstone/ |title=Jimmy Johnstone |website=Scottish Sports Hall of Fame |year=2002 |accessdate=7 December 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151005153923/http://www.sshf.co.uk/inductees/g-k/jimmy-johnstone/ |archive-date=5 October 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* [[Jimmy McGrory]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sshf.co.uk/inductees/l-p/jimmy-mcgrory/ |title=Jimmy McGrory |website=Scottish Sports Hall of Fame |year=2004 |accessdate=7 December 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Billy McNeill]] [[Member of the Most Excellent Order of the British Empire|MBE]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sshf.co.uk/inductees/l-p/billy-mcneill-mbe/ |title=Billy McNeill, MBE |website=Scottish Sports Hall of Fame |year=2002 |accessdate=7 December 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Jock Stein]] [[CBE]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sshf.co.uk/inductees/q-u/jock-stein-cbe/ |title=Jock Stein, CBE |website=Scottish Sports Hall of Fame |year=2004 |accessdate=7 December 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n{{For|a full list of honours including minor, reserve and youth competitions|list of Celtic F.C. records and statistics#Honours}}\n\n===Domestic honours===\n[[File:Celtic FC trophy case.JPG|thumb|right|Trophy case at [[Celtic Park]]]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Celtic Football Club \u2013 honours|url=http://spfl.co.uk/clubs/celtic/#honours|website=SPFL|accessdate=1 August 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"celthons\">{{cite web|title=About Celtic|url=http://www.celticfc.net/pages/about|website=Celtic FC|accessdate