ref>\n* {{Flagicon|Scotland}} [[Ronnie Simpson]]\n* {{Flagicon|Scotland}} [[Danny McGrain]]\n* {{Flagicon|Scotland}} [[Tommy Gemmell]]\n* {{Flagicon|Scotland}} [[Bobby Murdoch]]\n* {{Flagicon|Scotland}} [[Paul McStay]] \n* {{Flagicon|Scotland}} [[Billy McNeill]]&nbsp;\u2013 Voted Celtic's greatest ever captain\n* {{Flagicon|Scotland}} [[Bertie Auld]]\n* {{Flagicon|Scotland}} [[Jimmy Johnstone]]&nbsp;\u2013 Voted Celtic's greatest ever player\n* {{Flagicon|Scotland}} [[Bobby Lennox]] \n* {{Flagicon|Scotland}} [[Kenny Dalglish]]\n* {{Flagicon|Sweden}} [[Henrik Larsson]]&nbsp;\u2013 Voted Celtic's greatest ever foreign player\n\n==Club officials==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Board of directors===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Position<ref>{{cite web|title=Corporate \u2013 Board of Directors|url=http://www.celticfc.net/pages/corporate_boardofdirectors|website=Celtic FC|accessdate=30 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Appointment of Financial Director|url=http://www.celticfc.net/news/9612|accessdate=30 May 2016|work=Celtic FC|date=27 November 2015}}</ref>!! Name\n|-\n|Chairman || [[Ian Bankier]]\n|-\n|Chief Executive || [[Peter Lawwell]]\n|-\n|Financial director || Chris McKay\n|-\n|Senior independent director || Tom Allison\n|-\n|Independent non-executive director || Sharon Brown\n|-\n|Independent non-executive director || [[Dermot Desmond]]\n|-\n|Independent non-executive director || [[Brian Wilson (Labour politician)|Brian Wilson]]\n|-\n|Company secretary || Michael Nicholson\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Management===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Position !! Name\n|-\n|Manager|| [[Neil Lennon]]\n|-\n|Assistant Manager || [[John Kennedy (Scottish footballer)|John Kennedy]]\n|-\n|First Team Coach || [[Damien Duff]]\n|-\n|Goalkeeping Coach || [[Stevie Woods (footballer)|Stevie Woods]]\n|-\n|Head of Football Operations || [[Nick Hammond]]\n|-\n|Chief Scout || [[Peter Houston]]\n|-\n|Head of Sports Science || Jack Nayler\n|-\n|Physio || Tim Williamson\n|-\n|Head of Professional Academy || [[Tommy McIntyre]]\n|-\n|Head of Youth Academy || [[Chris McCart]]\n|-\n|Reserve Team Coach || [[Stephen McManus]]\n|-\n|Under 18s Manager || [[Darren O'Dea]]\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n===Managerial history===\n\n[[File:FC Salzburg versus Celtic FC (4. Oktober 2918 Gruppe B, Zweiter Spieltag) 13.jpg|thumb|right|upright|Brendan Rodgers led Celtic to a unique unbeaten domestic treble in the [[2016\u201317 Celtic F.C. season|2016\u201317]] season]]\n\n{{Main|List of Celtic F.C. managers}}\n{|\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|\n{| class=\"wikitable alternance\"\n|+<ref>{{cite web|title=Celtic \u2013 Managers|url=http://www.soccerbase.com/teams/team.sd?team_id=512&teamTabs=managers|website=Soccerbase|accessdate=28 August 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n!|Name\n!|Period\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Scotland}} [[Willie Maley]] || 1897\u20131940\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Scotland}} [[Jimmy McStay]] || 1940\u20131945\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Scotland}} [[Jimmy McGrory]] || 1945\u20131965\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Scotland}} [[Jock Stein]] || 1965\u20131978\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|{{flagicon|Scotland}} [[Billy McNeill]] || 1978\u20131983\n|-\n| 1987\u20131991\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Scotland}} [[David Hay]] || 1983\u20131987\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Ireland}} [[Liam Brady]] || 1991\u20131993\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Scotland}} [[Lou Macari]] || 1993\u20131994\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Scotland}} [[Tommy Burns (footballer)|Tommy Burns]] || 1994\u20131997\n|}\n|\n{| class=\"wikitable alternance\"\n|+&nbsp;\n|-\n!|Name\n!|Period\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Netherlands}} [[Wim Jansen]] || 1997\u20131998\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Slovakia}} [[Jozef Venglo\u0161]] || 1998\u20131999\n|-\n|{{flagicon|England}} [[John Barnes (footballer)|John Barnes]] || 1999\u20132000\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Northern Ireland}} [[Martin O'Neill]] || 2000\u20132005\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Scotland}} [[Gordon Strachan]] || 2005\u20132009\n|-\n|{{flagicon|England}} [[Tony Mowbray]] || 2009\u20132010\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|{{flagicon|Northern Ireland}} [[Neil Lennon]] || 2010\u20132014\n|-\n| 2019\u2013\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Norway}} [[Ronny Deila]] || 2014\u20132016\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Northern Ireland}} [[Brendan Rodgers]] || 2016\u20132019\n|}\n|}\n\n==Halls of Fame==\n\n===Scotland Football Hall of Fame===\nAs of 1 June 2019, 27 Celtic players and managers have entered the [[Scottish Football Hall of Fame]]:<ref>{{cite web |url=http://scottishfootballhalloffame.co.uk/hall-of-fame/ |title=Hall of Fame |work=The Scottish Football Hall of Fame |accessdate=19 December 2018}}</ref>\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-3}}\n* [[Roy Aitken]]\n* [[Bertie Auld]]\n* [[Stevie Chalmers]]\n* [[John Clark (footballer, born 1941)|John Clark]]\n* [[Jim Craig (Scottish footballer)|Jim Craig]]\n* [[Paddy Crerand]]\n* [[Kenny Dalglish]] [[MBE]]\n* [[Jimmy Delaney]]\n* [[Bobby Evans]]\n{{col-3}}\n* [[Tommy Gemmell]]\n* [[Mo Johnston]]\n* [[Jimmy Johnstone]]\n* [[Paul Lambert]]\n* [[Henrik Larsson]]\n* [[Bobby Lennox]]\n* [[Willie Maley]]\n* [[Danny McGrain]]\n* [[Jimmy McGrory]]\n{{col-3}}\n* [[Billy McNeill]]\n* [[Paul McStay]]\n* [[Bobby Murdoch]]\n* [[Charlie Nicholas]]\n* [[Ronnie Simpson]]\n* [[Jock Stein]] [[CBE]]\n* [[Gordon Strachan]]\n* [[John Thomson (footballer, born 1909)|John Thomson]]\n* [[Willie Wallace]]\n{{col-end}}\n\n===Scotland Roll of Honour===\nThe [[Scotland national football team roll of honour]] recognises players who have gained 50 or more international caps for Scotland. Inductees to have played for Celtic are:<ref name=SFARoll>{{cite web|url=http://www.scotlandfootballstats.co.uk/players/sfa-hall-of-fame |work=Scotland Football Stats |accessdate=27 February 2017|title=SFA Hall of Fame}}</ref>\n\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n* [[Roy Aitken]] (50)\n* [[Tom Boyd (Scottish footballer)|Tom Boyd]] (66)\n* [[Scott Brown (footballer, born June 1985)|Scott Brown]] (52)\n* [[Gary Caldwell]] (17)\n* [[John Collins (footballer born 1968)|John Collins]] (32)\n{{col-2}}\n* [[Kenny Dalglish]] [[MBE]] (47)\n* [[Craig Gordon]] (14)\n* [[Danny McGrain]] [[MBE]] (62)\n* [[Paul McStay]] (76)\n* [[Kenny Miller]] (7)\n{{col-end}}\n\nNumbers in brackets indicate the number of caps the above players won whilst at Celtic.<ref name = \"lh\">{{cite web |url=http://www.fitbastats.com/scotland/domestic_caps_per_player.php?club=42 |work=Fitbastats |title=Players Capped When Playing With Celtic |accessdate=19 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Scottish Sports Hall of Fame===\nIn the [[Scottish Sports Hall of Fame]], five Celtic players have been selected, they are:\n\n* [[Knight Bachelor|Sir]] [[Kenny Dalglish]] [[MBE]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sshf.co.uk/inductees/a-f/kenny-dalglish-mbe/ |title=Kenny Dalglish, MBE |website=Scottish Sports Hall of Fame |year=2002 |accessdate=7 December 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151005143759/http://www.sshf.co.uk/inductees/a-f/kenny-dalglish-mbe/ |archive-date=5 October 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* [[Jimmy Johnstone]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sshf.co.uk/inductees/g-k/jimmy-johnstone/ |title=Jimmy Johnstone |website=Scottish Sports Hall of Fame |year=2002 |accessdate=7 December 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151005153923/http://www.sshf.co.uk/inductees/g-k/jimmy-johnstone/ |archive-date=5 October 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* [[Jimmy McGrory]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sshf.co.uk/inductees/l-p/jimmy-mcgrory/ |title=Jimmy McGrory |website=Scottish Sports Hall of Fame |year=2004 |accessdate=7 December 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Billy McNeill]] [[MBE]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sshf.co.uk/inductees/l-p/billy-mcneill-mbe/ |title=Billy McNeill, MBE |website=Scottish Sports Hall of Fame |year=2002 |accessdate=7 December 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Jock Stein]] [[CBE]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sshf.co.uk/inductees/q-u/jock-stein-cbe/ |title=Jock Stein, CBE |website=Scottish Sports Hall of Fame |year=2004 |accessdate=7 December 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n{{For|a full list of honours including minor, reserve and youth competitions|list of Celtic F.C. records and statistics#Honours}}\n\n===Domestic honours===\n[[File:Celtic FC trophy case.JPG|thumb|right|Trophy case at [[Celtic Park]]]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Celtic Football Club \u2013 honours|url=http://spfl.co.uk/clubs/celtic/#honours|website=SPFL|accessdate=1 August 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"celthons\">{{cite web|title=About Celtic|url=http://www.celticfc.net/pages/about|website=Celtic FC|accessdate=11 May 2016}}</ref>\n\n* '''[[List of Scottish football champions|Scottish League Championship]]: 50'''\n:: [[1892\u201393 Scottish Football League|1892\u201393]], [[1893\u201394 Scottish Division One|1893\u201394]], [[1895\u201396 Scottish Division One|1895\u201396]], [[1897\u201398 Scottish Division One|1897\u201398]], [[1904\u201305 Scottish Division One|1904\u201305]], [[1905\u201306 Scottish Division One|1905\u201306]], [[1906\u201307 Scottish Division One|1906\u201307]], [[1907\u201308 Scottish Division One|1907\u201308]], [[1908\u201309 Scottish Division One|1908\u201309]], [[1909\u201310 Scottish Division One|1909\u201310]], [[1913\u201314 Scottish Division One|1913\u201314]], [[1914\u201315 Scottish Division One|1914\u201315]], [[1915\u201316 Scottish Division One|1915\u201316]], [[1916\u201317 Scottish Division One|1916\u201317]], [[1918\u201319 Scottish Division One|1918\u201319]], [[1921\u201322 Scottish Division One|1921\u201322]], [[1925\u201326 Scottish Division One|1925\u201326]], [[1935\u201336 Scottish Division One|1935\u201336]], [[1937\u201338 Scottish Division One|1937\u201338]], [[1953\u201354 Scottish Division One|1953\u201354]], [[1965\u201366 Scottish Division One|1965\u201366]], [[1966\u201367 Scottish Division One|1966\u201367]], [[1967\u201368 Scottish Division One|1967\u201368]], [[1968\u201369 Scottish Division One|1968\u201369]], [[1969\u201370 Scottish Division One|1969\u201370]], [[1970\u201371 Scottish Division One|1970\u201371]], [[1971\u201372 Scottish Division One|1971\u201372]], [[1972\u201373 Scottish Division One|1972\u201373]], [[1973\u201374 Scottish Division One|1973\u201374]], [[1976\u201377