rs.<ref name=\"beavers17\">{{cite news | last1=Beavers | first1=Olivia | title=Report: Conyers Settled Wrongful Dismissal Complaint over 'Sexual Advances' | url=http://thehill.com/homenews/house/361301-report-conyers-settled-wrongful-dismissal-complaint-over-sexual-advances | work=[[The Hill (newspaper)|The Hill]] | date=November 20, 2017 | quote=Conyers \u2026 reportedly settled a wrongful dismissal complaint in 2015 after a former employee accused him of firing her for resisting his \u2018sexual advances\u2019&nbsp;... Conyers\u2019s office did not immediately respond to a request for comment from The Hill.}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | last=Singman | first=Brooke | url=http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2017/11/21/house-ethics-committee-launches-probe-into-john-conyers-allegations.html | title=Ethics panel probes Conyers allegations, as Dem leaders call claims 'disturbing' | date=November 21, 2017 | publisher=Fox News | access-date=November 21, 2017}}</ref>\n*Staff Fred W. Pagan (R) to US Senator [[Thad Cochran]] (R-MS) pled guilty to possession of methamphetamine and GBL with intent to distribute and was sentenced to 30 months in prison. (2016)<ref name=\"auto2\">{{cite web | title=Ex-aide to Sen. Thad Cochran receives 30-month sentence in D.C. drug case | website=Washington Post | date=2016-01-20 | url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/ex-aide-to-sen-thad-cochran-receives-30-month-sentence-in-dc-drug-case/2016/01/20/16d13376-bf8b-11e5-83d4-42e3bceea902_story.html | access-date=2019-09-14}}</ref><ref name=\"auto3\">{{cite web | title=Staffer for Senator Thad Cochran Arrested on Drug Charges | website=NBC News | date=2015-04-25 | url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/staffer-senator-thad-cochran-arrested-drug-charges-n348136 | access-date=2019-09-14}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Hess|first=Hannah | title=Cochran Staffer Confesses to Sex-for-Drugs Scheme, Feds Say | website=Roll Call | date=2015-04-24 | url=https://www.rollcall.com/news/cochran-staffer-confesses-